history.text: I can't believe it's been so long since Wonder Woman came out! have you seen the movie?
I think Gal Gadot is beautiful and strong, and it's worth seeing the movie just for her performance!
No, I haven't seen it yet but I have been interested in giving it a try
It's apparently a spin from her appearance in 2016's Batman v Superman
So I'll probably need to watch Batman v Superman first then
Does the movie have a good plot?
Would it be something intended for children?

IT seems interesting. It's about a princess (wonder woman) 
living int he Amazon who saves Steve Trevor (an american)
It's set in WW1 which is interesting too.
I think it may be a little violent for children.
Did you know that it's the first super hero movie to be directed by a woman?
No I didn't
Yes. It was directed by Patty Jenkins
Well I think that would make it even better
Definitely!
About how long does the movie last?
IT got great reviews too. 92% on Rotten Tomatoes
I'm not sure how long the movie is. The plot seems a little complex though so it probably isn't short
It also has some allusions to Greek Mythology (Zeus)
I'll have to check the critics then, I always like to check comments before viewing a movie
Me too. Metacritic has it at 76/100
and CinemaScore is A
I love a movie with greek mythology
Are there any other well known actors that play in it
Chris Pine is the male protaganist. He is the American solider rescued by Wonder Woman in the beginning
And Robin Wright plays Antiope, another Greek mythology character
So it seems to be a lot of women in this one.
i think that would make for a great spin off to show the strong women super heroes
Definitely. It looks like the Greek God Ares is the villan
He apparently wants to destroy mankind and tries to recruit Wonder Woman to help him do it
Because he wants things to go back to "paradise"
so do you believer this movie will keep me entertained all the way through
I think so. There's definitely a lot going on. And it seems like there are some pretty epic battle scenes which are always cool.
Wonder Woman at some point has a weapon called a "Godkiller" sword lol
it's not too much going on is it? movies that jump around too much tend to make me lose interest
It doesn't seem like TOO much. Just enough to keep you engaged. There's even a reference to Bruce Wayne near the end
So you think its going to lead up to another story line? maybe another sequel
Oh definitely. Apparently she is thanking him via email for a gift he sent her, and reaffirming her mission to fight for the world.

uid2response.feedback: the other user was very detailed and answered every question with an appropriate response. I will most likely see this movie.
